('UK (England, Wales, Scotland, Northern Ireland)', 'Millennium Cohort Study', 'MCS', 'The Millennium Cohort Study provides longitudinal data on around 19,000 young people born between 2000 and 2002 in England, Scotland, Wales, and Northern Ireland. Their physical, cognitive, behavioral, and socio-emotional development is tracked with measurements taken nearly every year. Data is accessible from the website of the study.', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'Pure longitudinal', 'Hybrid', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'Every three years', 2001, 'ongoing', 'National', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'Mixed (computer and paper-based)', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 14318, 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No Access or Limited Access Under Specific Conditions', 'On a personal computer without a specific interface', 'https://cls.ucl.ac.uk/cls-studies/millennium-cohort-study/', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Not clear', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Not clear', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Not clear', 'Yes', 'Both self-reported and administrative', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes, precise number', 'Yes, for both parents', 'Yes, detailed information (e.g. ISCO code) for both parents', 'Yes, for both parents', 'Yes, simplified ISCED for both parents', 'Yes, for both parents', 'Yes', 'Yes, specific country', 'Yes', 'Not clear', 'Not clear', 'Not clear', 'Yes', 'Both self-reported and administrative', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Self-reported (provided by teachers)', 'Linkable to the ones of students', 'Not clear', 'Yes', 'Not clear', 'Not clear', 'Not clear', 'Not clear', 'Not clear'),
