('NL (Netherlands)', 'The Netherlands Cohort Study on Education', 'NCO', 'The Netherlands Cohort Study on Education (NCO) provides longitudinal data spanning 14 years on students in primary and secondary education across a national sample, and the exams assess literacy, numeracy, a foreign language, and one selected additional subject (Biology, Chemistry, Physics). Data access is granted upon request to researchers affiliated with institutions authorized for remote access through Statistics Netherlands (CBS), a basic cost of €1,800 is applied.', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'Pure longitudinal', 'Hybrid', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Yearly (or more than once per year)', 2010, 'ongoing', 'National', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'Paper-based', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'N/A', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Full access through request', 'On a personal computer with a specific interface', 'https://www.nationaalcohortonderzoek.nl/', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'Administrative (provided by the institution or others)', 'Yes', 'Not clear', 'Yes, precise number', 'Yes, for both parents', 'Yes, simplified information for both parents', 'Yes, for both parents', 'Yes, simplified ISCED for both parents', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Administrative (provided by the institution or others)', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Not clear', 'Not clear', 'Yes', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No'),
('HU (Hungary)', 'Országos Kompetenciamérés (National Assessment of Basic Competencies)', 'NABC', 'Since 2001, Hungary’s National Assessment of Basic Competencies (NABC) has collected annual standardized test data in reading comprehension and mathematics for all students in grades 6, 8, and 10. The dataset includes contextual variables and covers the full student population. Microdata are not publicly accessible and remain unavailable to external researchers.', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'Pseudo-panel', 'Hybrid', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Yearly (or more than once per year)', 2001, 'ongoing', 'National', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'Mixed (computer and paper-based)', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'N/A', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No Access or Limited Access Under Specific Conditions', 'Not clear', 'https://www.oktatas.hu/kozneveles/meresek/digitalis_orszagos_meresek/hatterkerdoiv https://www.oktatas.hu/kozneveles/meresek/digitalis_orszagos_meresek/lebonyolitas/tudnivalok_idei_orsz_meresekrol_2023_2024/felmeresvezetoi_utmutatok', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'Both self-reported and administrative', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Not clear', 'Yes, for both parents', 'Yes, simplified information for both parents', 'Yes, for both parents', 'Yes, simplified ISCED for both parents', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'Self-reported (provided by the students)', 'Yes', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'Self-reported (provided by teachers)', 'Not clear', 'Not clear', 'Yes', 'Not clear', 'No', 'No', 'Not clear', 'Not clear'),
('UK (England, Wales, Scotland, Northern Ireland)', 'COVID Social Mobility and Opportunities ', 'COSMO', 'COSMO is a major national longitudinal study which is examining the unequal impacts of the COVID-19 pandemic and its aftermath on the life chances of a generation of young people. Spanning two waves it tracks over 13,000 students in England capturing data on educational inequality, wellbeing, and life chances amid COVID-19 and the cost-of-living crisis. Wave 1 and 2 data are accessible via the UK Data Service.', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Pure longitudinal', 'Survey', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yearly (or more than once per year)', 2021, 'ongoing', 'Limited to specific regions/areas', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'Not clear', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 14000, 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'Open data', 'On a personal computer without a specific interface', 'https://cosmostudy.uk', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'Not clear', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'Self-reported (provided by the student)', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes, precise number', 'Yes, only for one parent', 'Yes, detailed information (e.g. ISCO code) for both parents', 'Yes, for both parents', 'Yes, full ISCED for both parents', 'Yes, for both parents', 'Yes', 'Yes, specific country', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'Self-reported (provided by the students)', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Not clear', 'Not clear', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No'),
('IE (Ireland)', 'Children''s School Lives', 'CSL', 'The Children’s School Lives (CSL) study is Ireland’s first national longitudinal study of primary education, following over 4,000 children across 189 schools from 2019 to 2024. Conducted by UCD for the NCCA, it gathers test (reading and mathematics), survey and interview data from students, families, and educators. ', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'Pure longitudinal', 'Survey', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Yearly (or more than once per year)', 2019, 2024, 'National', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', NULL, 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'Not clear', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 4000, 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Not clear', 'Not clear', 'https://cslstudy.ie/', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Not clear', 'Not clear', 'Not clear', 'Not clear', 'Not clear', 'Not clear', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Not clear', 'Not clear', 'Not clear', 'Not clear', 'Not clear', 'Not clear', 'Not clear', 'Not clear', 'Not clear', 'Not clear', 'Yes, only for one parent', 'Yes, simplified information for only one parent', 'Yes, only for one parent', 'Not clear', 'Yes, only for one parent', 'Yes', 'Yes, geographical area', 'Not clear', 'Not clear', 'Yes', 'Not clear', 'Not clear', 'Self-reported (provided by the students)', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Self-reported (provided by teachers)', 'Not clear', 'Not clear', 'Yes', 'Not clear', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Not clear'),
('UK (England, Wales, Scotland, Northern Ireland)', 'National Pupil Database', 'NPD', 'The National Pupil Database (NPD) is a comprehensive administrative dataset covering 19 years of education, skills, and children’s services data for all learners in England. It includes exam results in literacy, numeracy, foreign languages, and sciences or humanities. Data access is available via application to the Department for Education (DfE).', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'Pure longitudinal', 'Administrative', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Yearly (or more than once per year)', 2002, 'ongoing', 'National', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'Not clear', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'N/A', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No Access or Limited Access Under Specific Conditions', 'On a personal computer with a specific interface', 'https://www.find-npd-data.education.gov.uk/', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Not clear', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Administrative (provided by the institution or others)', 'No', 'No', 'Yes, precise number', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Administrative (provided by the institution or others)', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Administrative (provided by the institution or others)', 'Not linkable to the ones of students', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No'),
('PT (Portugal)', 'Observatório de Trajetos dos Estudantes do Ensino Secundário', 'OTES', 'The Observatório de Trajetos dos Estudantes do Ensino Secundário (OTES) is a longitudinal survey tracking secondary students in Portugal from 2007 and ongoing. It covers 10th–12th grade students across academic, technological, artistic, and vocational tracks. Assessments include reading, math, physics, and chemistry. Microdata access requires on-site presence at DGEEC, the data owner; linkages to administrative data are limited to data owners.', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'Pure longitudinal', 'Survey', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Yearly (or more than once per year)', 2007, 'ongoing', 'National', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'Mixed (computer and paper-based)', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'N/A', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No Access or Limited Access Under Specific Conditions', 'On a computer belonging to the producer of the data, which is not connected to internet or to another computer (in this case the producer examines all the results outputs)', 'https://www.dgeec.medu.pt/pag/6499de939eff36f307f07bdc/65524fc0455255473193d2bd/65524fef455255473193d2bf', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'Yes', 'Not clear', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'Not clear', 'Yes', 'No', 'Self-reported (provided by the student)', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'Yes, for both parents', 'Yes, simplified information for both parents', 'Yes, for both parents', 'Yes, full ISCED for both parents', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Self-reported (provided by the students)', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Not clear', 'Not clear', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No');
