('PT (Portugal)', 'Escola 360 ', 'E360', 'Escola 360 (E360) is a centralized student management system established in 2014 by Portugal’s Ministry of Education. It covers all levels from pre-school to secondary education. Microdata access requires physical presence at the facilities of DGEEC, the data owner, and is subject to strict access conditions.', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'Repeated cross-section', 'Administrative', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Yearly (or more than once per year)', 2014, 'ongoing', 'National', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'Not clear', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'N/A', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No Access or Limited Access Under Specific Conditions', 'On a computer belonging to the producer of the data, which is not connected to internet or to another computer (in this case the producer examines all the results outputs)', 'https://e360.edu.gov.pt/', 'Yes', 'Not clear', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'Not clear', 'Not clear', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Administrative (provided by the institution or others)', 'Not clear', 'No', 'Yes, precise number', 'Yes, only for one parent', 'Yes, detailed information (e.g. ISCO code) for only one parent', 'Yes, only for one parent', 'Yes, simplified ISCED for only one parent', 'No', 'No', 'Yes, specific country', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Not clear', 'No', 'Administrative (provided by the institution or others)', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Administrative (provided by the institution or others)', 'Linkable to the ones of students', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'No'),
('PT (Portugal)', 'Sistema Integrado de Informação e Gestão da Oferta Educativa e Formativa', 'SIGO', 'The Sistema Integrado de Informação e Gestão da Oferta Educativa e Formativa (SIGO) is an administrative dataset in Portugal, active since 2000. It covers all school grades, from primary to post-secondary education and adult training. Microdata access requires on-site presence at DGEEC and linkage to other administrative data is restricted to data owners.', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'Repeated cross-section', 'Administrative', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Yearly (or more than once per year)', 2000, 2021, 'National', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'Not clear', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'N/A', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No Access or Limited Access Under Specific Conditions', 'On a computer belonging to the producer of the data, which is not connected to internet or to another computer (in this case the producer examines all the results outputs)', 'https://www.sigo.pt/Login.jsp', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Not clear', 'Not clear', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Administrative (provided by the institution or others)', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Not clear', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Not clear', 'Not clear', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No'),
('IE (Ireland)', 'Growing Up in Ireland, Infant Cohort', 'GUI (IC)', 'Growing Up in Ireland – Cohort ’08 is a national longitudinal study tracking over 11,000 children from 9 months old, beginning in 2008. Follow-ups were conducted at ages 3, 5, 7/8 (postal), 9, and 13, with work at age 17 underway. It covers multiple life domains, including education. Anonymised microdata are available upon request.', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'Pure longitudinal', 'Hybrid', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'Every four year or more', 2007, 'ongoing', 'National', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'Mixed (computer and paper-based)', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 11134, 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Full access through request', 'On a personal computer without a specific interface', 'https://www.growingup.gov.ie/', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Both self-reported and administrative', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes, precise number', 'Yes, for both parents', 'No', 'Yes, for both parents', 'No', 'Yes, for both parents', 'Yes', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Administrative (provided by the institution or others)', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'Self-reported (provided by teachers)', 'Linkable to the ones of students', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Not clear', 'Not clear', 'Not clear'),
('IE (Ireland)', 'Growing up in Ireland, Child cohort', 'GUI (CC)', 'Child Cohort (IE) - The Growing Up in Ireland – Child Cohort began in 2008 with 8,500 nine-year-olds. Data were collected from children, parents, teachers, principals, and others involved in their care. Follow-ups occurred at ages 13, 17/18, and 20, with data from age 25 currently being prepared. Anonymised microdata are available upon request.', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'Pure longitudinal', 'Hybrid', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'Every four year or more', 2007, 'ongoing', 'National', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'Mixed (computer and paper-based)', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 8568, 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Full access through request', 'On a personal computer without a specific interface', 'https://www.growingup.gov.ie/', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Both self-reported and administrative', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes, precise number', 'Yes, for both parents', 'No', 'Yes, for both parents', 'No', 'Yes, for both parents', 'Yes', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Self-reported (provided by the students)', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'Self-reported (provided by teachers)', 'Linkable to the ones of students', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Not clear', 'Not clear', 'Not clear'),
('UK (England, Wales, Scotland, Northern Ireland)', 'Growing Up in Scotland, Birth cohort 1', 'GUS (BC1)', 'Growing Up in Scotland’s Birth Cohort 1 follows 5,217 children born between June 2004 and May 2005. Data were collected from age 10 months to 17 years, with the latest wave at age 19/20 underway in 2025. The study includes linked health and education records. Anonymised microdata are available upon request.', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'Pure longitudinal', 'Survey', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'Every other year', 2005, 'ongoing', 'National', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'Computer-based', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 5217, 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Full access through request', 'On a personal computer without a specific interface', 'https://growingupinscotland.org.uk', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'Yes', 'Not clear', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Not clear', 'Yes', 'Not clear', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Not clear', 'Self-reported (provided by the student)', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes, precise number', 'Yes, for both parents', 'Not clear', 'Yes, for both parents', 'Yes, full ISCED for both parents', 'Yes, for both parents', 'Yes', 'Yes, specific country', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Not clear', 'Yes', 'Self-reported (provided by the students)', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Not clear', 'Not clear', 'Not clear', 'Not clear', 'Not clear', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No'),
('UK (England, Wales, Scotland, Northern Ireland)', 'Growing Up in Scotland, Birth cohort 2', 'GUS (BC2)', 'Birth Cohort 2 (UK) - Birth Cohort 2 of Growing Up in Scotland includes around 6,127 children born between March 2010 and February 2011. Data were collected at ages 10 months, just under 3, and just under 5. The final sweep took place in 2015/16, and no further data collection is planned. Anonymised data are available upon request.', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'Pure longitudinal', 'Survey', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'Every other year', 2010, 2015, 'National', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'Not clear', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 6127, 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Full access through request', 'On a personal computer without a specific interface', 'https://growingupinscotland.org.uk/', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Not clear', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Not clear', 'Yes', 'Not clear', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Not clear', 'Not clear', 'Not clear', 'Self-reported (provided by the student)', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes, precise number', 'Yes, for both parents', 'Not clear', 'Yes, for both parents', 'Yes, full ISCED for both parents', 'Yes, for both parents', 'Yes', 'Yes, specific country', 'Yes', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Self-reported (provided by the students)', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Not clear', 'Not clear', 'Not clear', 'Not clear', 'Not clear', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes'),
('UK (England, Wales, Scotland, Northern Ireland)', 'Growing Up in Scotland, Child cohort', 'GUS (CC)', 'Growing Up in Scotland (GUS) is a major longitudinal study tracking the lives of children and their families. Child Cohort, launched in 2005, includes 2,858 children born between June 2002 and May 2003. Four waves of data were collected from just under age 3 to just under age 6. Anonymised data are available upon request.', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'Pure longitudinal', 'Survey', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yearly (or more than once per year)', 2005, 2009, 'National', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'Not clear', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 2858, 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Full access through request', 'On a personal computer without a specific interface', 'https://growingupinscotland.org.uk', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'Not clear', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Not clear', 'Yes', 'Not clear', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Not clear', 'Self-reported (provided by the student)', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes, precise number', 'Yes, for both parents', 'Not clear', 'Yes, for both parents', 'Yes, full ISCED for both parents', 'Yes, for both parents', 'Yes', 'Yes, specific country', 'Yes', 'No', 'Yes', 'Not clear', 'Yes', 'Self-reported (provided by the students)', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Not clear', 'Not clear', 'Not clear', 'Not clear', 'Not clear', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No'),
('DE (Germany)', 'Transformation des Sekundarschulsystems und akademische Karrieren (2002)', 'TOSCA (2002)', 'TOSCA-2002 is a longitudinal study examining the educational outcomes of 4,730 upper secondary graduates from 90 general and 59 vocational high schools in Baden-Württemberg during the 2001/02 school year. Follow-up surveys were conducted every two years until 2012, with a final wave in 2016. Data include information on school reform impacts, core subject assessments (Math or English), and school leadership characteristics. Data cover transitions to higher education and vocational training. Access is available upon request.', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'Repeated cross-section', 'Survey', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Every other year', 2002, 'ongoing', 'Limited to specific regions/areas', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'Not clear', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 4730, 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Not clear', 'Not clear', 'https://uni-tuebingen.de/fakultaeten/wirtschafts-und-sozialwissenschaftliche-fakultaet/faecher/fachbereich-sozialwissenschaften/hector-institut-fuer-empirische-bildungsforschung/forschung/aktuelle-studien/tosca/', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'Self-reported (provided by the student)', 'No', 'No', 'Yes, precise number', 'Yes, for both parents', 'Yes, detailed information (e.g. ISCO code) for both parents', 'Yes, for both parents', 'Yes, full ISCED for both parents', 'Yes, for both parents', 'No', 'Yes, specific country', 'Yes', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'Self-reported (provided by the students)', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Self-reported (provided by teachers)', 'Not clear', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No'),
('DE (Germany)', 'Transformation des Sekundarschulsystems und akademische Karrieren (2006)', 'TOSCA (2006)', 'TOSCA-2006 is the second cohort of the TOSCA study, following 5,016 upper secondary graduates from over 150 Gymnasiums in Baden-Württemberg, first surveyed in 2006. Follow-up postal surveys were conducted every two years until 2012, with a final wave in 2016. The study tracks educational and career pathways over a 10-year period. Data access is available upon request.', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'Pure longitudinal', 'Survey', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Every other year', 2006, 'ongoing', 'Limited to specific regions/areas', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'Not clear', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 5016, 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Not clear', 'Not clear', 'https://uni-tuebingen.de/fakultaeten/wirtschafts-und-sozialwissenschaftliche-fakultaet/faecher/fachbereich-sozialwissenschaften/hector-institut-fuer-empirische-bildungsforschung/forschung/aktuelle-studien/tosca/', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'Self-reported (provided by the student)', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes, precise number', 'Yes, for both parents', 'Yes, detailed information (e.g. ISCO code) for both parents', 'Yes, for both parents', 'Yes, full ISCED for both parents', 'Yes, for both parents', 'No', 'Yes, specific country', 'Yes', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'Self-reported (provided by the students)', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Self-reported (provided by teachers)', 'Not clear', 'Not clear', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No'),
('HU (Hungary)', 'KRTK’S Linked administrative panel dataset - Admin3', 'KRTK''S Admin3', 'Admin4 is a linked administrative panel dataset developed by KRTK covering all pupils from 2007 to 2021. It integrates data from multiple administrative sources to track individuals’ educational and labor market trajectories over time. The dataset enables longitudinal analysis but is not publicly accessible; data access is available upon request and subject to approval.', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'Repeated cross-section', 'Hybrid', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Yearly (or more than once per year)', 2003, 2017, 'National', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'Not clear', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'N/A', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Full access through request', 'On a personal computer with a specific interface', 'https://adatbank.krtk.mta.hu/en/adatbazisok/elerheto-adatbazisok/', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Not clear', 'Both self-reported and administrative', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Not clear', 'Yes, for both parents', 'Yes, simplified information for both parents', 'Yes, for both parents', 'Yes, simplified ISCED for both parents', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'Both self-reported and administrative', 'Yes', 'No', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'No', 'Self-reported (provided by teachers)', 'Linkable to the ones of students', 'Not clear', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Yes', 'Not clear', 'Not clear');
